"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89806","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-09-04","<p> </p><p>My Department spent £3,543.20 on new televisions in 2013 when the Northern Ireland Office moved from Millbank to new offices at 1 Horse Guards Road. This move will deliver a saving to the taxpayer in the region of £1m per year.</p><p>There has been no expenditure on the purchase of televisions in 2014 to date.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-09-04T11:30:07.1893773Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89806/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89806/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89806/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-08-29","Television","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how much her Department spent on the purchase of televisions in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","207222"
