"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89827","Department for Transport","false","2014-09-04","<p> </p><p>The Maritime and Coastguard Agency’s activities for each financial and operating year are set out in its published Business Plans. These set out the Agency’s total budget for the delivery of its work, including efforts to promote the safety of seafarers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>However no specific budgetary allocation has been or will be earmarked for this activity.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2014-09-04T13:46:09.4905728Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89827/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89827/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89827/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-08-29","Shipping: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the Maritime and Coastguard Agency's (MCA) annual budget for promoting seafarer safety to ship owners operating in the UK was in each year since 2009-10; and what the MCA's budget for such work is in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Katy Clark","North Ayrshire and Arran","Katy Clark","207105"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89828","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-09-05","<p /> <p>Bail conditions are recorded on HMCTS’ case management systems as a free text field. As each condition is a unique data entry and there is no common field that could be aggregated to enable central collation they cannot answer this question. The only way it could be answered would be to manually check every case where conditional bail has been granted at any point during the case and check both the conditions and the offence or offences. This would incur disproportionate costs.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-09-05T14:54:54.9330924Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89828/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89828/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/89828/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-08-29","Dangerous Driving","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many drivers charged with dangerous driving offences were made to surrender their licence as a condition of bail in the last year.","false","Biography information for Richard Graham","Gloucester","Richard Graham","207113"
