"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79665","Home Office","false","2014-09-22","<p /> <p>The Home Office does not routinely comment on individual cases. This is because the Home Office has obligations in law to protect this information. The Liberation and Justice Movement of Sudan has not been proscribed by the UK. Individuals associated with the Liberation and Justice Movement would not necessarily be denied entry based solely on their association with it.</p><p />",,"Lord Bates",,"2014-09-22T11:35:21.0948678Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79665/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79665/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79665/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-28","Sudan","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether anyone associated with the Liberation and Justice Movement of Sudan has been barred from entering the United Kingdom; and, if so, who and why.","false","Biography information for Lord Ashcroft",,"Lord Ashcroft","HL1557"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79666","Department for International Development","false","2014-08-11","<p> </p><p>The Offering Memorandum sent by the Turks and Caicos Islands (TCI) Government for a bond issue guaranteed by DFID in 2011 is not a document owned by her Majesty’s Government. It would therefore not have been appropriate for DFID to place a copy of it in the Library of the House, although my previous answer did make clear that the Noble Lord could obtain a copy of the document by requesting it from the TCI Government.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Freedom of Information requests cover documents held by Her Majesty’s Government. DFID therefore sought the consent of the TCI Government before agreeing to release the TCI document.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Northover",,"2014-08-11T10:32:12.3601046Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79666/answer","Biography information for Baroness Northover","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79666/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79666/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-28","Turks and Caicos Islands","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answers by Baroness Northover on 23 June (WA 136) and 8 July (WA 40), why the request to place a document in the Library of the House was refused yet it was released under a Freedom of Information request.","false","Biography information for Lord Ashcroft",,"Lord Ashcroft","HL1558"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79667","Department for Education","false","2014-07-30","<p>The Department for Education does not hold data relating to local authority practice with regards to live birth data. The statutory guidance for children’s centres is clear that health services and local authorities should share information, such as live birth data, with children’s centres on a regular basis.</p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2014-07-30T11:21:39.9682325Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79667/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79667/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79667/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-07-28","Children's Centres","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many local authorities are not currently sharing live birth data with children’s centres in their areas.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Listowel",,"The Earl of Listowel","HL1559"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79668","Department for Education","false","2014-07-30","<p>As set out in the Department for Education’s Sure Start Children’s Centres statutory guidance, health services and local authorities should share information, such as live birth data and data on families with children under five who have recently moved into the area, effectively with children’s centres on a regular basis. Local authorities and commissioners of health services should consider developing local partnership agreements or information sharing protocols to enable effective sharing of bulk data (such as live birth data), whilst ensuring that the requirements of the Data Protection Act 1998, and other relevant legal provisions, are complied with.</p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2014-07-30T13:31:21.1385564Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79668/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79668/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79668/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-07-28","Children's Centres","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether parental consent is necessary for local authorities to share live birth data with Sure Start Children’s Centres.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Listowel",,"The Earl of Listowel","HL1560"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79669","Department for Education","false","2014-07-30","<p>The Government has no plans to review the statutory guidance on the sharing of live birth data.</p><p>The Department for Education’s statutory guidance for children’s centres is clear that health services and local authorities should share information, such as live birth data, with children’s centres on a regular basis. It is important that professionals work together to identify families who are in need of support and offer them that support.</p>",,"Lord Nash","HL1562","2014-07-30T11:37:52.8468073Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79669/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79669/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79669/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-07-28","Childbirth","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they intend to review the statutory guidance on the sharing of live birth data.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Listowel",,"The Earl of Listowel","HL1561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79670","Department for Education","false","2014-07-30","<p>The Government has no plans to review the statutory guidance on the sharing of live birth data.</p><p>The Department for Education’s statutory guidance for children’s centres is clear that health services and local authorities should share information, such as live birth data, with children’s centres on a regular basis. It is important that professionals work together to identify families who are in need of support and offer them that support.</p>",,"Lord Nash","HL1561","2014-07-30T11:37:53.4155523Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79670/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79670/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79670/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-07-28","Children's Centres","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they are taking to ensure that all local authorities share live birth data with children’s centres in their area.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Listowel",,"The Earl of Listowel","HL1562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79671","Cabinet Office","false","2014-08-11","<p>Big Society hands people control in their local communities so that they can take action to shape where they live and help others. Volunteering is up 6% since 2010 and 80,000 young people have taken part in National Citizen Service since 2011, contributing over 2 million hours of social action to their local communities.</p><p>The Localism Act has resulted in over 1,200 assets of community value being listed and we have helped 150 organisations to acquire a community asset or obtain significant investment towards doing so. More than 900 neighbourhood planning areas have been designated, and all 28 plans which have reached referendum so far have passed with significant majorities in favour.</p><p> </p><p>This Government is committed to opening up public services so that social enterprises and voluntary organisations can play an increased role in delivering local services. We are introducing legislation that will require the public sector to publish details on the value of new contracts awarded to VCSEs, as part of Lord Young's reforms to make public procurement more accessible to smaller businesses.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Wallace of Saltaire","HL1564 ; HL1565 ; HL1566 ; HL1567","2014-08-11T11:20:53.0914842Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79671/answer","Biography information for Lord Wallace of Saltaire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79671/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79671/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-28","Third Sector","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what they have learnt from promoting the Big Society.","false","Biography information for Lord Mawson",,"Lord Mawson","HL1563"
